<PubmedArticle><MedlineCitation Status="MEDLINE" Owner="NLM" IndexingMethod="Automated"><PMID Version="1">41538903</PMID><DateCompleted><Year>2026</Year><Month>02</Month><Day>06</Day></DateCompleted><DateRevised><Year>2026</Year><Month>03</Month><Day>04</Day></DateRevised><Article PubModel="Print-Electronic"><Journal><ISSN IssnType="Electronic">1578-8989</ISSN><JournalIssue CitedMedium="Internet"><Volume>166</Volume><Issue>1</Issue><PubDate><Year>2026</Year><Month>Jan</Month></PubDate></JournalIssue><Title>Medicina clinica</Title><ISOAbbreviation>Med Clin (Barc)</ISOAbbreviation></Journal><ArticleTitle>Prognostic factors and predictive models for outcomes in organophosphate poisoning: A retrospective analysis.</ArticleTitle><Pagination><StartPage>107329</StartPage><MedlinePgn>107329</MedlinePgn></Pagination><ELocationID EIdType="doi" ValidYN="Y">10.1016/j.medcli.2025.107329</ELocationID><ELocationID EIdType="pii" ValidYN="Y">S0025-7753(25)00557-3</ELocationID><Abstract><AbstractText Label="PURPOSE">This study aimed to identify prognostic factors and develop a predictive model for patients with organophosphate poisoning.</AbstractText><AbstractText Label="METHODS">A retrospective analysis of 108 cases was conducted, collecting demographic, clinical, and laboratory data including age, sex, time to treatment, plasma organophosphate (OP) levels, arterial lactate (LAC), aspartate aminotransferase (AST), creatinine (Cr), and Acute Physiology and Chronic Health Evaluation II (APACHE II) scores. Patients were categorized into survivor and non-survivor groups. Multivariate logistic regression and receiver operating characteristic (ROC) analyses were performed to identify independent prognostic factors and assess their predictive value.</AbstractText><AbstractText Label="RESULTS">The overall mortality rate was 23.15%. Non-survivors had higher age, LAC, AST, Cr, and APACHE II scores, and lower AChE levels compared to survivors. Multivariate logistic regression identified age (OR: 1.12, 95% CI: 1.05-1.22) and AST (OR: 1.03, 95% CI: 1.01-1.05) as independent prognostic factors. ROC analysis validated a model combining age, AChE, and AST, showing an excellent discriminative ability with an AUC of 0.95 (95% CI: 0.91-0.99), sensitivity of 1.00, and specificity of 0.90.</AbstractText><AbstractText Label="CONCLUSIONS">Age and AST are significant prognostic factors for organophosphate poisoning. Combining these factors enhances predictive accuracy, aiding clinical decision-making and emphasizing early aggressive management to improve survival rates.</AbstractText><CopyrightInformation>Copyright &#xa9; 2025. Published by Elsevier Espa&#xf1;a, S.L.U.</CopyrightInformation></Abstract><AuthorList CompleteYN="Y"><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Sun</LastName><ForeName>Liang</ForeName><Initials>L</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Department of Immunology, Characteristic Medical Center of the Chinese People's Armed Police Force, 220#, Cheng-Lin Road, Tianjin 300162, China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Bao</LastName><ForeName>Buhe</ForeName><Initials>B</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Department of Medical Equipment Management, Characteristic Medical Center of the Chinese People's Armed Police Force, 220#, Cheng-Lin Road, Tianjin 300162, China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Zhang</LastName><ForeName>Yu-Hua</ForeName><Initials>YH</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Department of Respiratory Medicine, Characteristic Medical Center of the Chinese People's Armed Police Force, 220#, Cheng-Lin Road, Tianjin 300162, China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Du</LastName><ForeName>Zhenhua</ForeName><Initials>Z</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Department of Laboratory Medicine, Characteristic Medical Center of the Chinese People's Armed Police Force, 220#, Cheng-Lin Road, Tianjin 300162, China. Electronic address: dzhtoms@163.c